WEBVTT

00:00.967 --> 00:04.569
♪♪

00:04.604 --> 00:06.772
Thank you so much, Zecora!

00:06.807 --> 00:10.075
I never would have found the
crisscross moss without you!

00:10.110 --> 00:11.276
Of course!

00:11.311 --> 00:14.379
<i>I know where it grows</i>
<i>so it's not much to ask.</i>

00:14.414 --> 00:17.716
<i>Though retrieving it has</i>
<i>been a difficult task.</i>

00:17.751 --> 00:20.419
Oh, but the oxen visiting
Sweetfeather Sanctuary

00:20.454 --> 00:22.654
next week will surely
appreciate it!

00:22.689 --> 00:25.290
It really adds a
shine to their coat.

00:28.261 --> 00:32.164
<i>There we go. Now, that</i>
<i>wasn't so tough.</i>

00:32.199 --> 00:35.567
<i>Fluttershy tell me,</i>
<i>will this be enough?</i>

00:35.602 --> 00:40.105
Gee, I don't know, it's
a pretty big pack,

00:40.140 --> 00:41.606
so maybe enough to
fill up this sack?

00:41.641 --> 00:44.242
[giggle] Oh, my!

00:44.277 --> 00:46.611
You're rubbing
off on me, Zecora!

00:46.646 --> 00:49.848
♪♪

00:49.883 --> 00:51.416
[shouts]

00:51.451 --> 00:52.684
[splash]

00:52.719 --> 00:53.585
[scream]

00:54.554 --> 00:56.088
Oh, no, oh no, oh no!

00:56.123 --> 00:57.522
[gasp]

00:57.557 --> 00:59.724
Zecora! Are you all right?

00:59.759 --> 01:03.195
<i>No need to fret,</i>
<i>I only got wet...</i>

01:03.230 --> 01:05.363
<i>At least now I can easily grab</i>

01:05.398 --> 01:07.566
<i>all the crisscross moss</i>
<i>there is to be had!</i>

01:11.304 --> 01:12.271
[poof]

01:14.774 --> 01:18.443
[gasp]
What's happening to you?

01:18.478 --> 01:21.146
<i>Honestly, it's hard to tell,</i>

01:21.181 --> 01:24.316
<i>but suddenly I</i>
<i>don't feel so well.</i>

01:27.154 --> 01:28.153
[horrified gasp]

01:31.558 --> 01:34.860
<i>♪ My little pony,</i>
<i>my little pony ♪</i>

01:34.895 --> 01:36.828
<i>♪ Aaaahhh ♪</i>

01:36.863 --> 01:38.864
<i>♪ My little Pony ♪</i>

01:38.899 --> 01:41.466
<i>♪ I used to wonder what</i>
<i>friendship could be. ♪</i>

01:41.501 --> 01:43.335
<i>♪ My Little Pony ♪</i>

01:43.370 --> 01:45.770
<i>♪ Until you all shared</i>
<i>its magic with me. ♪</i>

01:45.805 --> 01:47.806
<i>♪ Big adventure! ♪</i>
<i>♪ Tons of fun ♪</i>

01:47.841 --> 01:50.175
<i>♪ A beautiful heart! ♪ ♪</i>
<i>Faithful and strong! ♪</i>

01:50.210 --> 01:52.310
<i>♪ Sharing kindness ♪</i>
<i>♪ it's an easy feat ♪</i>

01:52.345 --> 01:54.346
<i>♪ And magic makes it</i>
<i>all complete! ♪</i>

01:54.381 --> 01:56.448
<i>♪ To have my little pony ♪</i>

01:56.483 --> 01:59.751
<i>♪ Do you know you're all</i>
<i>my very best friends? ♪</i>

01:59.786 --> 02:01.753
♪♪

02:11.865 --> 02:13.598
All right, Zecora,

02:13.633 --> 02:16.501
let's have a listen to
the ol' ticker!

02:16.536 --> 02:17.669
<i>♪ [jazz drumming] ♪</i>

02:17.704 --> 02:19.905
Hmmm...

02:19.940 --> 02:20.739
Hmmm.

02:20.774 --> 02:22.741
Do you think it's
serious, Doctor?

02:22.776 --> 02:25.644
Well, that wasn't a good sign.

02:25.679 --> 02:27.679
I can't believe a
<u>flower</u> did this!

02:27.714 --> 02:30.348
I take back thinking
it was pretty!

02:30.383 --> 02:31.884
[coughing]

02:36.990 --> 02:40.759
We're looking for any
color other than red.

02:40.794 --> 02:42.861
Phew!

02:42.896 --> 02:44.563
[huge gasp]

02:44.598 --> 02:47.866
Oh! It's just as I thought.

02:47.901 --> 02:52.971
I'm afraid you have a very rare
disease called ...Swamp Fever.

02:53.006 --> 02:55.407
[thunderclap]

02:55.442 --> 02:58.310
<i>Tell me, Doctor,</i>
<i>what should I do?</i>

02:58.345 --> 03:01.213
<i>I've never heard of</i>
<i>Swamp Fever, mind you.</i>

03:01.248 --> 03:04.516
Unfortunately, very little is
known about the disease,

03:04.551 --> 03:06.818
except, of course, its symptoms:

03:06.853 --> 03:08.720
change of coat,
coughing bubbles,

03:08.755 --> 03:12.424
shock sneezing, confusion
and the last stage...

03:12.459 --> 03:14.993
The afflicted turn
into the very trees

03:15.028 --> 03:17.762
that drop the disease-
spreading flower.

03:17.797 --> 03:19.364
Oh!

03:19.399 --> 03:21.366
<i>Is there anything</i>
<i>that can be done?</i>

03:21.401 --> 03:23.802
<i>For such a terrible</i>
<i>conundrum?</i>

03:23.837 --> 03:26.705
A cure has yet to be discovered.

03:26.740 --> 03:28.807
I'm sorry, Zecora.

03:28.842 --> 03:30.408
Hmmm.

03:30.443 --> 03:32.611
It's a lot to take in.

03:32.646 --> 03:34.346
I'll leave you
two to discuss.

03:34.381 --> 03:36.014
[slam]

03:36.049 --> 03:38.750
Zecora, this is
all my fault!

03:38.785 --> 03:40.885
If you hadn't been helping
me get the crisscross moss,

03:40.920 --> 03:43.288
you wouldn't have
gotten Swamp Fever!

03:43.323 --> 03:45.757
I'm so sorry.

03:45.792 --> 03:48.326
<i>Fluttershy, you</i>
<i>are not to blame.</i>

03:48.361 --> 03:50.662
<i>These things happen,</i>
<i>all the same.</i>

03:50.697 --> 03:52.664
I refuse to accept that!

03:52.699 --> 03:54.933
There has to be<u> somepony</u>
who can help you.

03:54.968 --> 03:57.335
Oh!

03:57.370 --> 04:00.438
<i>There's a healer of legend</i>
<i>who never would fail.</i>

04:00.473 --> 04:03.375
<i>But I only know her</i>
<i>from ancient folk tales.</i>

04:03.410 --> 04:06.411
<i>Mystical and masked,</i>
<i>she came in the night</i>

04:06.446 --> 04:09.681
<i>and cured everything from</i>
<i>hoof cough to fur blight.</i>

04:09.716 --> 04:12.450
<i>What became of the</i>
<i>healer, nopony knows,</i>

04:12.485 --> 04:15.754
<i>for she disappeared</i>
<i>ages and ages ago.</i>

04:15.789 --> 04:18.690
The Mystical Mask, of course!

04:18.725 --> 04:21.926
My parents would tell me about
her whenever I was sick in bed.

04:21.961 --> 04:24.462
<i>There's so many accounts</i>
<i>of her power to heal</i>

04:24.497 --> 04:27.599
<i>She can't just be a legend.</i>
<i>I think she's real.</i>

04:27.634 --> 04:31.036
If that's who we need to cure
you, then I'm going to find her!

04:31.071 --> 04:32.871
And I know just the
pony who can help!

04:34.507 --> 04:36.408
[panting]

04:36.443 --> 04:37.309
Twilight!

04:38.445 --> 04:39.378
Twilight!

04:41.047 --> 04:42.614
Twilight!

04:42.649 --> 04:45.016
Oh, I'm so sorry
to bother--

04:45.051 --> 04:47.852
are... are you cooking?

04:47.887 --> 04:50.422
Yeah, Spike and I are
having a cook-off.

04:50.457 --> 04:51.956
My cauliflower bites blew
her sweet potato muffins

04:51.991 --> 04:53.792
out of the water!

04:53.827 --> 04:55.460
I'm glad you're
here, Fluttershy,

04:55.495 --> 04:58.430
because we're going to need
a second opinion about that.

04:58.465 --> 05:01.533
[munching]

05:01.568 --> 05:03.935
Um...they're both
delicious. But ...

05:03.970 --> 05:05.670
Zecora has Swamp Fever
and there's no cure

05:05.705 --> 05:07.539
and it's all my fault
and the only pony

05:07.574 --> 05:09.040
who can cure her is
the Mystical Mask

05:09.075 --> 05:11.343
and I need your
help to find her!

05:11.378 --> 05:13.878
So what'd she pick? The
cauliflower bites, right?

05:13.913 --> 05:16.915
♪♪

05:23.623 --> 05:25.790
That's the last book
on ancient ponies

05:25.825 --> 05:28.460
and still no mention of
the Mystical Mask.

05:28.495 --> 05:31.563
Hmm, did we check the
unabridged versions?

05:31.598 --> 05:33.431
Yes. And the books
on rare diseases,

05:33.466 --> 05:34.866
the books on rare plants

05:34.901 --> 05:37.602
and the entire section
on bog habitation.

05:37.637 --> 05:39.738
Well, we might have to look
through every book

05:39.773 --> 05:43.641
in the entire library, but I
know we'll figure it out!

05:43.676 --> 05:44.876
Oh!

05:44.911 --> 05:46.912
♪♪

05:53.853 --> 05:56.154
Oh, another dead end.

05:56.189 --> 05:57.956
Have you found
anything yet, Twilight?

05:57.991 --> 05:59.491
[snoring]
-Twilight?

05:59.526 --> 06:00.525
Ah! [crash]

06:00.560 --> 06:01.993
Goodness, are you OK?

06:02.028 --> 06:04.763
[sigh] I'm
fine.

06:04.798 --> 06:07.599
Fluttershy, you know that
I want to help Zecora.

06:07.634 --> 06:10.502
But I think we'd be a lot better
off if we got some sleep.

06:10.537 --> 06:12.404
We've been at this for hours.

06:12.439 --> 06:14.406
Oh, I'm so sorry!

06:14.441 --> 06:16.441
I didn't realize how
late it had gotten!

06:16.476 --> 06:17.909
No problem.

06:17.944 --> 06:19.177
I'll grab you
a pillow and--

06:19.212 --> 06:21.813
Oh, no no no, I meant
<u>you</u> should sleep.

06:21.848 --> 06:25.183
I can't rest until
Zecora is healed!

06:25.218 --> 06:28.086
I understand how you feel, but I
still think we'd have more luck

06:28.121 --> 06:30.622
if we tried again
in the morning.

06:30.657 --> 06:32.824
Just promise me you'll
take a break soon.

06:32.859 --> 06:34.759
Mm-hmm.

06:34.794 --> 06:35.960
[yawn]

06:35.995 --> 06:37.129
Good night, Fluttershy.

06:40.467 --> 06:43.101
9 by 13 inch pan...

06:43.136 --> 06:44.636
Twilight!

06:44.671 --> 06:46.838
Non-stick pans!

06:46.873 --> 06:50.074
What's all the commotion
in here, ladies?

06:50.109 --> 06:53.077
Sorry! But I figured out
who the Mystical Mask is.

06:53.112 --> 06:55.046
[gasp] You did?

06:55.081 --> 06:56.581
All I had to do was
cross-reference

06:56.616 --> 06:58.049
a book about masks
with another book

06:58.084 --> 06:59.717
on ancient
Equestrian healers,

06:59.752 --> 07:01.553
then use a third book
to translate it all

07:01.588 --> 07:02.987
from Old Ponish
and there it was!

07:03.022 --> 07:04.456
Zecora was right!

07:04.491 --> 07:06.858
The Mystical Mask
wasn't just a legend.

07:06.893 --> 07:09.727
The Mystical Mask
was MAGE MEADOWBROOK!

07:09.762 --> 07:11.729
[gasp]

07:11.764 --> 07:14.098
The ancient sorceress
from Hayseed Swamp?

07:14.133 --> 07:16.100
We studied her at
Celestia's school.

07:16.135 --> 07:17.469
Are you sure?

07:17.504 --> 07:18.937
Absolutely!

07:18.972 --> 07:20.972
Mage Meadowbrook wasn't
just a sorceress,

07:21.007 --> 07:22.740
she was also a
healer and back then,

07:22.775 --> 07:25.844
healers wore masks so they
wouldn't get sick themselves!

07:25.879 --> 07:28.913
Fluttershy, I am so
incredibly proud of you

07:28.948 --> 07:31.950
for using your research
skills to figure this out!

07:31.985 --> 07:34.018
But... Meadowbrook
lived ages ago and...

07:34.053 --> 07:35.720
Didn't she disappear?

07:35.755 --> 07:37.689
Mm hm. But if we go
to Hayseed Swamp,

07:37.724 --> 07:39.624
maybe we can find
something she left behind.

07:39.659 --> 07:41.759
Something that could
lead to a cure!

07:41.794 --> 07:44.796
It seems like a long shot,
but I guess it's possible.

07:46.699 --> 07:49.133
We have to try! I've got
our route all planned out

07:49.168 --> 07:51.169
and on the way we can
check up on Zecora--

07:51.204 --> 07:53.872
Whoa, whoa, whoa.
We're leaving<u> now?</u>

07:53.907 --> 07:54.873
Of course!

07:54.908 --> 07:56.241
Every second we spend waiting,

07:56.276 --> 07:58.877
is a second Zecora
is coughing bubbles!

07:58.912 --> 08:00.778
But Fluttershy,
you haven't slept.

08:00.813 --> 08:02.580
And that's a long journey.

08:02.615 --> 08:05.216
There's no use trying to talk
me out of this, Twilight!

08:05.251 --> 08:07.585
We've got no
time to waste!

08:07.620 --> 08:09.588
Can we at least
grab some breakfast?

08:11.024 --> 08:12.690
I packed cauliflower bites.

08:12.725 --> 08:15.226
Aww. No sweet
potato muffins?

08:15.261 --> 08:17.962
I.. uh.. ate them all.

08:17.997 --> 08:19.664
They were actually
really good.

08:25.305 --> 08:27.572
...and that's when I
realized the Mystical Mask

08:27.607 --> 08:30.575
was actually Mage
Meadowbrook!

08:30.610 --> 08:33.011
<i>That's marvelous, Fluttershy!</i>

08:33.046 --> 08:34.812
<i>I am quite impressed.</i>

08:34.847 --> 08:36.548
<i>While you're gone</i>
<i>on your journey</i>

08:36.583 --> 08:39.250
<i>I'll try not to be</i> ...<i> worried.</i>

08:39.285 --> 08:43.021
[gasp] Oh, no! Zecora,
you didn't rhyme!

08:43.056 --> 08:44.923
You must be getting worse!

08:44.958 --> 08:47.825
<i>No, no, no! Not at all...</i>

08:47.860 --> 08:50.628
<i>Something, something... ball?</i>

08:50.663 --> 08:51.930
Achoo!

08:53.633 --> 08:54.966
That's it!

08:55.001 --> 08:56.167
We have to go now!

08:56.202 --> 08:57.536
Lead the way, Fluttershy!

08:59.005 --> 08:59.871
[thud]

08:59.906 --> 09:00.972
[groan]

09:04.077 --> 09:06.077
♪♪

09:14.053 --> 09:19.324
[frogs croaking]

09:19.359 --> 09:23.094
So... where do you think
Meadowbrook lived?

09:23.129 --> 09:25.630
I'm not sure.

09:25.665 --> 09:28.299
Maybe there's
somepony we can ask.

09:28.334 --> 09:30.569
I think we might be
the only ponies here.

09:33.640 --> 09:36.341
Wait. I recognize that tree!

09:36.376 --> 09:40.244
♪♪

09:40.279 --> 09:42.714
Yes, this has to be it!

09:42.749 --> 09:45.216
It's just like the
illustrations of her home!

09:45.251 --> 09:47.786
Anypony who lives in
a tree is OK by me.

09:50.923 --> 09:52.890
[grunts]

09:52.925 --> 09:54.025
Phew!

09:54.060 --> 09:56.127
Well, if the doorway
is sealed up,

09:56.162 --> 09:57.996
we just have
to dig our way in.

09:58.031 --> 10:00.632
Back up, Twilight; I don't
want you to get hurt!

10:00.667 --> 10:03.134
[panting]

10:03.169 --> 10:04.869
Or we could try
the handle.

10:07.674 --> 10:10.241
It really blends
in with the bark.

10:10.276 --> 10:11.776
Easy to miss.

10:14.213 --> 10:18.049
Wow, it looks like this place
has been abandoned for years.

10:20.787 --> 10:22.887
Twilight! Look!

10:22.922 --> 10:26.891
It's the same kind of lily pad
that gave Zecora Swamp Fever!

10:26.926 --> 10:29.427
I wonder if Meadowbrook
was looking for a cure

10:29.462 --> 10:31.429
for Swamp Fever too.

10:31.464 --> 10:33.364
Do you think she found it?

10:33.399 --> 10:36.000
I hope so. But let's not
get ahead of ourselves.

10:36.035 --> 10:37.669
[high-pitched squeak]

10:37.704 --> 10:39.671
That's exactly what
I'm talking about.

10:39.706 --> 10:42.040
You're making your excited
squeaking noise.

10:42.075 --> 10:46.844
Uh, I wasn't making my
excited squeaking noise.

10:46.879 --> 10:48.179
[creaking]

10:48.214 --> 10:52.250
Ahhhhhhhhhh!!

10:52.285 --> 10:54.352
Y'all can stop screaming now.

10:54.387 --> 10:56.187
Didn't mean to scare ya.

10:56.222 --> 10:57.922
I do that a lot.

10:57.957 --> 10:59.190
Scare ponies?

10:59.225 --> 11:01.025
Or rock creepily in the dark?

11:01.060 --> 11:03.895
Well.. both, I s'pose.

11:03.930 --> 11:05.296
Name's Cattail.

11:05.331 --> 11:07.098
Pleased to meet ya!

11:07.133 --> 11:09.901
Likewise, but um, may I ask,

11:09.936 --> 11:12.203
why are you in Mage
Meadowbrook's home?

11:12.238 --> 11:14.939
Oh, I take care of the place.

11:14.974 --> 11:16.774
I ain't much of a cleaner.

11:16.809 --> 11:19.177
But from what I hear,
my kin wasn't either,

11:19.212 --> 11:23.114
so I doubt they'd mind a few
cobwebs in our ancestral home.

11:23.149 --> 11:25.817
You're related to
Mage Meadowbrook?

11:25.852 --> 11:27.385
Mm hm.

11:27.420 --> 11:29.353
Oh, my goodness,
Twilight, we did it!

11:29.388 --> 11:32.123
Not only did we find Mage
Meadowbrook's old house,

11:32.158 --> 11:34.859
we actually found one
of her descendants!

11:34.894 --> 11:37.228
Honestly, I would
not have guessed it.

11:37.263 --> 11:40.064
So, you lookin' for
some kind of cure, huh?

11:40.099 --> 11:42.834
Well, now, I know
Meadowbrook was known

11:42.869 --> 11:45.136
to always be writing
in her journals.

11:45.171 --> 11:48.406
If she had the cure you want,
I reckon that's where it'd be.

11:48.441 --> 11:51.142
Come on! I'll show
ya the library.

11:51.177 --> 11:53.478
Library? Now
we're talking!

11:57.917 --> 12:01.986
Oh. Well, libraries come
in all shapes and sizes.

12:02.021 --> 12:03.454
This is good!

12:03.489 --> 12:05.356
It'll take us less time
to go through everything.

12:09.896 --> 12:13.898
<i>"Today my mom made me eat peas.</i>
<i>Peas are yucky."</i>

12:13.933 --> 12:16.000
And... we can probably
skip this one.

12:16.035 --> 12:17.902
Unless she found a cure
when she was a foal...

12:17.937 --> 12:19.504
<i>"I met a colt today.</i>

12:19.539 --> 12:22.340
<i>He pulled my mane so I</i>
<i>put a frog on his head."</i>

12:22.375 --> 12:23.975
Also not helpful.

12:24.010 --> 12:26.010
But I do kind of want to
see where it goes.

12:29.282 --> 12:31.249
Wait, listen to this!

12:31.284 --> 12:34.419
<i>"Today, I tried again to</i>
<i>brew an un-sniffle elixir...</i>

12:36.489 --> 12:40.024
<i>" ... and I finally</i>
<i>got it right!</i>

12:40.059 --> 12:42.393
Achoo!

12:42.428 --> 12:44.028
[slurp]

12:44.063 --> 12:46.097
[sigh]

12:49.268 --> 12:51.836
Meadowbrook, I think
it's time you had this.

12:54.340 --> 12:57.074
My very own
healer's mask!

12:57.109 --> 12:58.409
You think I'm
ready, Mother?

12:58.444 --> 13:00.011
Mm hm.

13:00.046 --> 13:01.946
[knocking at door]

13:05.084 --> 13:06.384
What caused this?

13:08.521 --> 13:11.255
<i>Mother calls it "Swamp Fever".</i>

13:11.290 --> 13:15.193
<i>We've been trying to find a</i>
<i>cure, but it hasn't been easy.</i>

13:15.228 --> 13:17.395
[coughing]

13:17.430 --> 13:18.563
[knock at door]

13:18.598 --> 13:21.365
[coughing]

13:21.400 --> 13:23.367
<i>The fever's spread</i>
<i>like wild fire.</i>

13:23.402 --> 13:28.139
[coughing and sneezing]

13:28.174 --> 13:30.975
<i>I fear if we don't</i>
<i>find the cure soon,</i>

13:31.010 --> 13:35.012
<i>everypony will be</i>
<i>in grave danger...</i>

13:35.047 --> 13:37.915
[coughing]

13:37.950 --> 13:42.019
<i>With mother sick, I didn't</i>
<i>think I'd ever find a cure,</i>

13:42.054 --> 13:45.056
<i>but staring at those</i>
<i>cursed flowers today.</i>

13:45.091 --> 13:47.225
<i>I saw something...</i>

13:47.260 --> 13:49.260
♪♪

13:54.634 --> 13:56.234
Flash Bees!

13:59.171 --> 14:03.007
<i>I realized the flower's poison</i>
<i>didn't affect the Flash Bees</i>

14:03.042 --> 14:06.143
<i>and if they were</i>
<i>immune to Swamp Fever,</i>

14:06.178 --> 14:08.479
<i>their honey could be the cure!</i>

14:08.514 --> 14:11.115
<i>♪ [adventure theme] ♪</i>

14:11.150 --> 14:17.488
♪♪

14:17.523 --> 14:21.459
[buzzing]

14:21.494 --> 14:22.360
[snap]

14:30.336 --> 14:31.602
[thud]

14:31.638 --> 14:35.006
<i>But they were so aggressive</i>
<i>defending their hive,</i>

14:35.041 --> 14:37.242
<i>I didn't know how I</i>
<i>was going to get it!</i>

14:41.013 --> 14:43.147
Here goes nothin'!

14:48.454 --> 14:53.391
<i>Today I cured Mother and</i>
<i>the rest of the bayou.</i>

14:53.426 --> 14:56.227
<i>It was the greatest feeling</i>
<i>I've ever experienced</i>

14:56.262 --> 14:58.095
<i>and I promise to</i>
<i>dedicate my life</i>

14:58.130 --> 15:01.098
<i>to curing ponies all</i>
<i>over Equestria.</i>

15:01.133 --> 15:03.234
And she did
just that.

15:03.269 --> 15:06.604
Right up till she
disappeared without a trace.

15:06.639 --> 15:09.540
So all we have to do is find
those aggressive Flash Bees

15:09.575 --> 15:11.209
and get them to give
us their honey!

15:12.979 --> 15:15.380
Of course, it doesn't
say how she did that.

15:18.384 --> 15:20.518
What? Is my mane messy?

15:20.553 --> 15:22.587
I know I haven't slept
in a while but...

15:24.690 --> 15:29.127
Oh, no! I've caught
Swamp Fever!

15:34.000 --> 15:35.433
♪♪

15:35.468 --> 15:36.467
Huh?

15:36.502 --> 15:38.503
♪♪

15:41.741 --> 15:43.507
Are you sure these
are necessary?

15:43.542 --> 15:45.042
What?

15:45.077 --> 15:47.745
I said, are you sure
these are necessary?

15:47.780 --> 15:51.682
YES! I won't risk
infecting you or Cattail.

15:51.717 --> 15:54.185
What you can't risk
is getting any sicker.

15:54.220 --> 15:56.654
If you don't rest, your
symptoms will only get worse.

15:56.689 --> 15:58.189
[coughing]

15:58.224 --> 16:00.758
You really should rest
up before going up

16:00.793 --> 16:02.994
against those
Flash Bees.

16:03.029 --> 16:05.296
They are nasty critters.

16:05.331 --> 16:07.298
Um, you don't know
this about me,

16:07.333 --> 16:09.567
but I'm pretty
good with animals.

16:09.602 --> 16:11.569
And besides, Dogtail...

16:11.604 --> 16:13.437
Cattail.

16:13.472 --> 16:16.040
Um, Zecora is counting on me.

16:16.075 --> 16:18.776
I have to help her just like
Meadowbrook helped her mother

16:18.811 --> 16:21.278
and all those bayou
ponies long ago.

16:21.313 --> 16:23.347
But Fluttershy, as
much as Meadowbrook

16:23.382 --> 16:25.016
took care of other ponies,

16:25.051 --> 16:27.318
I'm sure she also
took care of herself!

16:27.353 --> 16:31.222
You're not going to
change my mind, Twilight!

16:31.257 --> 16:33.524
For being sick, she
sure is strong.

16:36.829 --> 16:40.598
Cattail: The Flash Bee
hive is just up yonder.

16:40.633 --> 16:42.800
Are you sure you don't
want me to come with you?

16:42.835 --> 16:45.336
No, it's too
dangerous, Twilight.

16:45.371 --> 16:48.305
Besides, I've already
gotten one friend hurt.

16:48.340 --> 16:50.541
I won't let it
happen to another.

16:50.576 --> 16:54.345
OK, Fluttershy.
You can do this!

16:54.380 --> 16:56.280
[coughing]

16:56.315 --> 16:58.382
[panting]

16:58.417 --> 17:01.152
<i>♪ [adventure] ♪</i>

17:01.187 --> 17:02.219
♪♪

17:02.254 --> 17:03.521
Mind over matter!

17:03.556 --> 17:05.556
♪♪

17:18.737 --> 17:20.538
[buzzing]

17:20.573 --> 17:22.573
Hello, Flash Bees!

17:22.608 --> 17:24.642
I was hoping I could
get some of your honey.

17:27.880 --> 17:29.647
Oh, I see.

17:29.682 --> 17:31.282
You don't let others have any.

17:31.317 --> 17:34.285
Well, I'm sorry, but
I<u> really</u> need it.

17:34.320 --> 17:36.320
[squeal]

17:36.355 --> 17:38.289
I didn't want it to
have to come to this

17:38.324 --> 17:40.124
but I'll just have to use...

17:40.159 --> 17:42.093
The Stare.

17:49.602 --> 17:50.534
[scream]

17:50.569 --> 17:51.802
[cough]

17:51.837 --> 17:53.370
You really are
aggressive.

17:53.405 --> 17:56.340
[intense coughing]

18:01.180 --> 18:02.146
Oh, dear.

18:07.486 --> 18:11.322
What happened? Where am I?

18:11.357 --> 18:13.657
I'm so glad you're OK!

18:13.692 --> 18:15.593
You're still in
Meadowbrook's tree.

18:15.628 --> 18:19.430
You fainted but Twilight shot
some magic up and caught ya.

18:19.465 --> 18:20.865
It was crazy.

18:20.900 --> 18:22.566
Goodness gracious!

18:22.601 --> 18:24.635
[coughing]

18:24.670 --> 18:25.903
Have you heard from Zecora?

18:25.938 --> 18:27.538
Is she OK?

18:27.573 --> 18:29.273
Uh...

18:29.308 --> 18:33.277
We got word your zebra friend
has started sprouting leaves.

18:33.312 --> 18:35.613
She's already
turning into a tree?

18:35.648 --> 18:37.515
I thought we'd
have more time.

18:37.550 --> 18:40.284
Actually, you've been
asleep for three days.

18:40.319 --> 18:41.752
Three days?

18:41.787 --> 18:43.854
Mm hm.

18:43.889 --> 18:46.223
You were asleep so long, we were
afraid you wouldn't be able

18:46.258 --> 18:47.691
to move when you woke up,

18:47.726 --> 18:49.860
but thankfully you just
wore yourself down.

18:49.895 --> 18:50.928
Oh, dear.

18:50.963 --> 18:52.696
We have to get
back to the hive.

18:52.731 --> 18:54.231
I've wasted so much time.

18:54.266 --> 18:56.467
Now hang on there,
Fluttershy,

18:56.502 --> 18:58.536
those Flash Bee
critters are tricky.

18:58.571 --> 18:59.803
Cattail's right.

18:59.838 --> 19:02.373
I can't even use magic
to calm them down.

19:02.408 --> 19:04.508
We'll have to find another
way to get the honey.

19:04.543 --> 19:07.278
We've tried everything
from disguises

19:07.313 --> 19:09.813
to things I won't
even speak of.

19:09.848 --> 19:11.448
[shudder]

19:11.483 --> 19:13.851
He's been through a lot
these past three days.

19:13.886 --> 19:14.885
Wait...

19:14.920 --> 19:16.587
disguises...

19:24.930 --> 19:26.897
[gasp] That's it!

19:26.932 --> 19:28.399
I know how she did it!

19:28.434 --> 19:29.867
I know how Meadowbrook
got the honey!

19:34.273 --> 19:37.942
<u>This</u> is how Meadowbrook got
the honey from the Flash Bees.

19:37.977 --> 19:40.211
She threw a mask at 'em?

19:40.246 --> 19:42.213
I wouldn't recommend that.

19:42.248 --> 19:45.616
No. The male bees aren't
aggressive around the queen bee

19:45.651 --> 19:48.786
and this mask has the same
stripes that she does!

19:48.821 --> 19:50.388
Fluttershy, that's brilliant!

19:52.324 --> 19:52.756
Achoo!

19:52.791 --> 19:54.758
Whoa!

19:54.793 --> 19:56.493
There's no time to waste!

19:56.528 --> 19:57.728
Hooves crossed!

19:59.999 --> 20:02.333
Oh, golly, I can't watch!

20:03.969 --> 20:05.236
[coughing]

20:05.271 --> 20:06.570
Mind over matter!

20:06.605 --> 20:11.375
♪♪

20:11.410 --> 20:13.777
[buzzing]

20:13.812 --> 20:19.283
[Fluttershy buzzes]

20:24.890 --> 20:26.523
Twilight!

20:26.558 --> 20:27.858
It's working!

20:37.870 --> 20:40.638
I think she's cured
now, Fluttershy.

20:40.673 --> 20:46.343
<i>Oh, I<u></u></i> <u>do</u> feel fine,
<i>and this honey is divine</i> .

20:46.378 --> 20:48.512
Oh, you're
rhyming again!

20:48.547 --> 20:50.948
Welcome back,
my friend!

20:50.983 --> 20:53.851
<i>Thank you Fluttershy,</i>
<i>for all you endured.</i>

20:53.886 --> 20:57.321
<i>If not for you, I</i>
<i>would not be cured.</i>

20:57.356 --> 20:59.390
If it wasn't for me,

20:59.425 --> 21:02.526
you wouldn't have been
sick in the first place!

21:02.561 --> 21:04.928
<i>Regret is not what</i>
<i>you should feel,</i>

21:04.963 --> 21:08.332
<i>because on this journey,</i>
<i>you've learned a great deal.</i>

21:08.367 --> 21:10.034
That's true.

21:10.069 --> 21:12.703
I certainly learned that if you
don't take care of yourself,

21:12.738 --> 21:15.572
you won't be able to take
care of anypony else.

21:15.607 --> 21:19.843
In fact, if I had rested, like
Twilight suggested all along,

21:19.878 --> 21:22.946
maybe I would have thought to
use Meadowbrook's mask sooner.

21:22.981 --> 21:25.983
[coughing]

21:26.018 --> 21:27.951
Please tell me you
found the cure.

21:27.986 --> 21:30.788
Achoo!
